    <section id="id21615442">
      <title>Memorandum</title>
      <para id="id19802770">Igneous rock</para>
      <para id="id19802774">1. cracks in the earth's crust</para>
      <para id="id21855780">Key</para>
      <para id="id10316348">2. earth's crust</para>
      <para id="id26258590">3. lava cools and solidifies as grey / black basalt </para>
      <para id="id24917037">4. red molten lava</para>
      <para id="id19873477">5. crater of the volcano</para>
      <para id="id15783628">6. magma forms lava</para>
      <para id="id21926893">Assignment 5:</para>
      <para id="id24798459">1. Magma (lava) will cool quickly as soon as it has erupted from the volcano and runs down the mountain slope</para>
      <para id="id26298506"><emphasis effect="bold">Reason:</emphasis> Little lava, exposed to the "cooler" atmosphere.</para>
      <para id="id21695078">2. Granite is found deep underneath the crust</para>
      <para id="id7571949"><emphasis effect="bold">Reason:</emphasis> Magma has to cool slowly in order to form granite.</para>
      <para id="id26265282">3. Deep underneath the earth's crust.</para>
      <para id="id9105944">4. Deep underneath the earth's crust.</para>
      <para id="id21256793"><emphasis effect="bold">Reason:</emphasis> The surrounding rocks keep the magma hot for a very long time. Therefore, it cannot cool quickly.</para>
      <para id="id22826144">5. Basalt is found on the slopes of the volcano.</para>
      <para id="id21240032"><emphasis effect="bold">Reason:</emphasis> Basalt forms when lava cools quickly. It has to be outside the crust.</para>
      <para id="id26325816">6. The smallest crystals appear in basalt - thus on the mountain slopes and valleys near the volcano.</para>
    </section>
